    <who name="Adam Williamson">awilliam</who>
    <bug_when>2017-01-16 21:25:59 -0500</bug_when>
    <thetext>Since anaconda-26.17-1, the user creation spoke shows an orange-bar warning if the password you set contains any non-ASCII characters. The English warning text reads:

&quot;The password you have provided contains non-ASCII characters. You may not be able to switch between keyboard layouts to login. Press Done to continue.&quot;

however, you can&apos;t actually press Done to continue. No matter how many times you click Done, the screen won&apos;t let you out unless you change the password not to contain any non-ASCII characters.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
